<div class="banner-container">
  <%= video_tag "drop.mp4", autoplay: true, loop: true, muted: "muted", class: "home_video" %>
  <div class="banner">
    <div class="banner-contents-container">
      <h1 class="home-h1">Rediscover Water</h1>
      <p>Find, log and rate waters from all over the world.</p>
      <%= render 'shared/search_form' %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

</div>

<div class="spacer-transparent">
</div>

<div class="container">
  <div class="row homepage-sommelier-row pb-2">
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-start">
      <div class="d-flex align-items-center sommelier-image-container">
        <%= image_tag "John-Berryman.jpg", class: "avatar-large", alt: "picture of sommelier" %>
      </div>
      <div class="sommelier-info-container">
        <h2>Our Sommelier's Top Picks this week</h2>
        <h3><strong>"</strong></h3><p>The waters for this week were grouped around the theme of alkalinity. Although usually associated
        with car batteries and ammonia, high pH in natural mineral waters contributes a distinctive tartness and
        dry mouthfeel that can be a welcome respite from the glut of mild, middle-pH waters on the market.
        <br>
        Try these waters with oily fish, samphire, or bitter seasonal greens. Foz paired beautifully with smoked Eel,
        Icelandic stood up against the intense salinity of samphire and grilled Bream, but would also go brilliantly with
        meatier fish, Bottarga, or any kind of roe. Lahuenco was a treat with buttered Cavolo Nero, and would also handsomely accompany Pak Choi.
        </p>
        <div class="info-footer row d-flex pr-4 justify-content-between">
          <p>-- Devon Ashberry - Lead Somm at WaterLog<p>
          <h3><strong>"</strong></h3>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <br>
  <div class="hr-container pr-2">
    <hr>
  </div>


  <div id="carouselExampleIndicators" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel" data-interval="10000">
    <ol class="carousel-indicators">
      <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
      <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="1"></li>
      <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="2"></li>
    </ol>
    <div class="carousel-inner">
      <div class="carousel-item active">
        <div class="row d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mt-5">
          <div class="sommeliers-comments-container col-sm-6 col-md-8 mt-3 pl-5 mb-5">
            <p>"Foz is quite a remarkable water. Naturally alkaline at a pH of 10.1, the Brazilian pick for this week
            accommodates a rare constellation of different minerals that make it highly conductive. That latent
            electrical energy is a joy to experience, and locks your subtle body into an aligned spiritual hum.
            Try it yourself - I'm not joking!"</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 mb-5 pl-0">
            <%= link_to water_path(@picked_water_1) do  %>
              <div class="card-bottle-tall">
                <div class="card-bottle-tall-image-container">
                  <%= image_tag @picked_water_1.photo %>
                </div>
                <div class="card-bottle-info">
                  <div class="card-bottle-info-container">
                    <p><%= @picked_water_1.name %></p>
                    <p><%= @picked_water_1.brand %></p>
                    <p><%= @picked_water_1.source %></p>
                    <p><%= @picked_water_1.country %></p>
                    <p>pH:<%= @picked_water_1.ph %></p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="carousel-item">
        <div class="row d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mt-5">
          <div class="sommeliers-comments-container col-sm-6 col-md-8 mt-3 pl-5 mb-5">
            <p>"The water of Ölfus spring, where Icelandic Glacial are based, arrives at the earth's
            surface having percolated, as rainfall and snowmelt, through endless layers of porous, igneous
          rock. That 5,000-year-long mineral-exposure yields a fantastic, and dare I say it, 'smoky' result.
        To top it off, the team at Icelandic are among the most sustainable in the industry."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 mb-5 pl-0">
            <%= link_to water_path(@picked_water_2) do  %>
              <div class="card-bottle-tall">
                <div class="card-bottle-tall-image-container">
                  <%= image_tag @picked_water_2.photo %>
                </div>
                <div class="card-bottle-info">
                  <div class="card-bottle-info-container">
                    <p><%= @picked_water_2.name %></p>
                    <p><%= @picked_water_2.brand %></p>
                    <p><%= @picked_water_2.source %></p>
                    <p><%= @picked_water_2.country %></p>
                    <p>pH:<%= @picked_water_2.ph %></p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="carousel-item">
        <div class="row d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mt-5">
          <div class="sommeliers-comments-container col-sm-6 col-md-8 mt-3 pl-5 mb-5">
            <p>"Soft and uniquely tannic, Lahuenco, like Foz, is drawn from a volcanic terroir. Unlike Foz, however, its water is extracted from the ground
            at a temperature of 21°. In Mapuche, 'lahuenco' means something like 'medicinal water', and it is this volcanic minerality
          and high natural temperature that no doubt have contributed such a reputation."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 mb-5 pl-0">
            <%= link_to water_path(@picked_water_3) do  %>
              <div class="card-bottle-tall">
                <div class="card-bottle-tall-image-container">
                  <%= image_tag @picked_water_3.photo %>
                </div>
                <div class="card-bottle-info">
                  <div class="card-bottle-info-container">
                    <p><%= @picked_water_3.name %></p>
                    <p><%= @picked_water_3.brand %></p>
                    <p><%= @picked_water_3.source %></p>
                    <p><%= @picked_water_3.country %></p>
                    <p>pH:<%= @picked_water_3.ph %></p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            <% end %>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#carouselExampleIndicators" role="button" data-slide="prev">
      <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
    </a>
    <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#carouselExampleIndicators" role="button" data-slide="next">
      <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
    </a>
  </div>



  <div class="hr-container pr-2">
    <hr>
  </div>
  <div class="mt-3" id="waters">
    <div class="row">
      <% @waters.each do |water| %>
        <div class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4 mb-5 pl-0">
          <%= link_to water_path(water) do  %>
            <div class="card-bottle-tall">
              <div class="card-bottle-tall-image-container">
                <%= image_tag water.photo %>
              </div>
              <div class="card-bottle-info">
                <div class="card-bottle-info-container">
                  <p><%= water.name %></p>
                  <p><%= water.brand %></p>
                  <p><%= water.source %></p>
                  <p><%= water.country %></p>
                  <p>pH:<%= water.ph %></p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<spacer class="spacer-transparent" type="horizontal" width="100" height="100"> ♢ </spacer>


